The time tracking funtionality of Jira would be much more useful for our  Project management if there was a high level summary of the remaining work available.

One way that is probably easy to implement would be to print a sum of the remaing work for each version in the roadmap, alongside the version status bar: "(38 of 42 issues are unresolved, 86 days of work remaining)"

Such a report would be a great help for scheduling release dates. Together with the release date per version feature mentioned in JRA-1012, this would really be fantastic, as it would allow us to continuously track whether our schedule is still realistic by just looking at the roadmap.

